ons is then offered on the psychological, theological, ethical, and metaphysical roots of humor—and its cruel rejection. "Like Aristotle and Dewey, Arnarsson and Baruchello do not define their terms at the outset, but instead they relentlessly pursue the meanings of two ordinary words that everyone vaguely understads to arrive at a critical insight into the concepts these words represent, which are both disparate and interrelated." - Richard Marc Rubin, President, George Santayana Society  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish literature. 0aImperialism in literature. 4aGrausamkeit. 4aHumor. 4aParadox. 4aSex. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aCruelty.  ahumour.  aparadox.  asex.1 aArnarsson, Ársæll Már, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1z978311133219208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023 Englishz978311131922308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023z9783111318646oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831112565730 cprintz978311125455540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311125610840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111256108423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111256108/original  a978-3-11-131922-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-133219-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1b2024  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_